<li id="cite_note-10"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFAndersen2020" class="citation news cs1">Andersen, Emily (July 21, 2020). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://universe.byu.edu/2020/07/21/the-color-of-christ-how-has-art-affected-racism-in-the-church/">"The color of Christ: How has art affected racism in the Church?"</a>. <i><a href="/wiki/Daily_Universe" class="mw-redirect" title="Daily Universe">Daily Universe</a></i>. <a href="/wiki/Brigham_Young_University" title="Brigham Young University">Brigham Young University</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Daily+Universe&amp;rft.atitle=The+color+of+Christ%3A+How+has+art+affected+racism+in+the+Church%3F&amp;rft.date=2020-07-21&amp;rft.aulast=Andersen&amp;rft.aufirst=Emily&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Funiverse.byu.edu%2F2020%2F07%2F21%2Fthe-color-of-christ-how-has-art-affected-racism-in-the-church%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMormon+teachings+on+skin+color" class="Z3988"></span></span>
