<li id="cite_note-BushDialogue-11"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-BushDialogue_11-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-BushDialogue_11-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-BushDialogue_11-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBush1973" class="citation journal cs1"><a href="/wiki/Lester_E._Bush_Jr." title="Lester E. Bush Jr.">Bush, Lester E.</a> (1973). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.dialoguejournal.com/wp-content/uploads/sbi/articles/Dialogue_V08N01_13.pdf">"Mormonism's Negro Doctrine: An Historical Overview"</a> <span class="cs1-format">(PDF)</span>. <i><a href="/wiki/Dialogue:_A_Journal_of_Mormon_Thought" title="Dialogue: A Journal of Mormon Thought">Dialogue</a></i>. <b>8</b> (1).</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Dialogue&amp;rft.atitle=Mormonism%27s+Negro+Doctrine%3A+An+Historical+Overview&amp;rft.volume=8&amp;rft.issue=1&amp;rft.date=1973&amp;rft.aulast=Bush&amp;rft.aufirst=Lester+E.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dialoguejournal.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fsbi%2Farticles%2FDialogue_V08N01_13.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMormon+teachings+on+skin+color" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-US_Commission_1959-12"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-US_Commission_1959_12-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-US_Commission_1959_12-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-US_Commission_1959_12-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation web cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=zKIHERHQKBcC&amp;pg=PA379">"The National Conference and the Reports of the State Advisory Committees to the U.S. Commission on Civil Rights"</a>. <a href="/wiki/United_States_Government_Publishing_Office" title="United States Government Publishing Office">United States Government Publishing Office</a>. 1959. pp.&#160;379–380 &#8211; via <a href="/wiki/Google_Books" title="Google Books">Google Books</a>. <q>The Mormon interpretation attributes birth into any race other than the white race as a result of inferior performance in a pre-earth life and teaches that by righteous living, the dark-skinned races may again become 'white and delightsome.' This doctrine is mentioned in passing by way of explaining certain attitudes evident in specific fields of investigation.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=The+National+Conference+and+the+Reports+of+the+State+Advisory+Committees+to+the+U.S.+Commission+on+Civil+Rights&amp;rft.pages=379-380&amp;rft.pub=United+States+Government+Publishing+Office&amp;rft.date=1959&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DzKIHERHQKBcC%26pg%3DPA379&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMormon+teachings+on+skin+color" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
