<li id="cite_note-Stone-35"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Stone_35-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFBushman2005" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Richard_Bushman" title="Richard Bushman">Bushman, Richard</a> (2005). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=Mz3tpz4eRBQC"><i>Joseph Smith: Rough Stone Rolling</i></a>. New York City: Knopf Doubleday Publishing Group. pp.&#160;97–98. <a href="/wiki/ISBN_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="ISBN (identifier)">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780307426482" title="Special:BookSources/9780307426482"><bdi>9780307426482</bdi></a>. <q>Not far into the story the Lamanites are marked with a dark skin ... This act resembles the curse of God on Cain in Genesis, the beginning, according to later Christian readings, of the Black race.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Joseph+Smith%3A+Rough+Stone+Rolling&amp;rft.place=New+York+City&amp;rft.pages=97-98&amp;rft.pub=Knopf+Doubleday+Publishing+Group&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.isbn=9780307426482&amp;rft.aulast=Bushman&amp;rft.aufirst=Richard&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DMz3tpz4eRBQC&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMormon+teachings+on+skin+color" class="Z3988"></span></span>
